  "title": "Operations and Maintenance Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor and operate streetlight systems (manual or smart/automated).</li>\n  <li>Perform preventive and corrective maintenance on poles, cables, lights, and control gear.</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely ON/OFF operations and fault rectification.</li>\n  <li>Maintain reports on faults, repairs, energy use, and inventory.</li>\n  <li>Ensure safety compliance and supervise technicians or contractors.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with municipal bodies, vendors, and utility providers.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Skills &amp; Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Electrical Engineering.</li>\n  <li>2–5 years of O&amp;M experience (preferably in lighting or electrical infrastructure).</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of LV systems, lighting controls, and safety standards.</li>\n</ul>",
